ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: gtin14
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: gtin8
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: guideline
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A medical guideline related to this entity.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: guideline subject
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has POS
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: headline
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Headline of the article

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: health condition
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Expectations for health conditions of target audience

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: height
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The height of the item.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: high price
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The highest price of all offers available.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hiring organization
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Organization offering the job position.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: home location
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A contact location for a person's residence.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: honorific prefix
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: honorific suffix
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An honorific suffix preceding a Person's name such as M.D. /PhD/MSCSW.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hospital affiliation
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: how performed
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: How the procedure is performed.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: identifying exam
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: identifying test
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: illustrator
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The illustrator of the book.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: imaging technique
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Imaging technique used.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in album
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The album to which this recording belongs.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in language
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The language of the content. please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in playlist
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: incentives
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: included risk factor
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: includes object
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: increases risk of
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: indication
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A factor that indicates use of this therapy for treatment and/or prevention of a condition, symptom, etc. For therapies such as drugs, indications can include both officially-approved indications as well as off-label uses. These can be distinguished by using the ApprovedIndication subtype of MedicalIndication.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: industry
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The industry associated with the job position.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: infectious agent
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: infectious agent class
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: ingredients
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An ingredient used in the recipe.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: insertion
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: intensity
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: interacting drug
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: interaction count
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A count of a specific user interactions with this item—for example, 20 UserLikes, 5 UserComments, or 300 UserDownloads. The user interaction type should be one of the sub types of UserInteraction.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: interactivity type
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: inventory level
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is accessory or spare part for
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is available generically
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is consumable for
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is family friendly
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is part of
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the collection or gallery to which the item belongs.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is proprietary
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is related to
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is similar to
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is variant of
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isbn
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The ISBN of the book.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isic v4
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: item condition
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: item list element
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A single list item.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: item list order
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: item offered
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The item being sold.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: item reviewed
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: job location
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: job title

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: keywords

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: knows

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: learning resource type

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: legal name

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: legal status

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: lesser

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: lesser or equal
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: line
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: location
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The location of the event or organization.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: longitude

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: low price

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: main content of page

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: makes offer
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: manufacturer
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The manufacturer of the product.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: max price
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The highest price if the price is a range.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: max value
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The upper of the product characteristic.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: maximum intake
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: mechanism of action
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: medical specialty
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A medical specialty of the provider.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: medicine system
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: member
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A member of this organization.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: member of

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: mentions
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: min price
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The lowest price if the price is a range.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: min value
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The lower value of the product characteristic.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: model
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: mpn
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: music by
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The composer of the movie or TV soundtrack.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: music group member
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A member of the music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: normal range
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: number of episodes
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The number of episodes in this season or series.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: nutrition
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Nutrition information about the recipe.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: occupational category
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Category or categories describing the job. Use BLS O*NET-SOC taxonomy: http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html. Ideally includes textual label and formal code, with the property repeated for each applicable value.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: offers
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An offer to sell this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, the DVD of a movie, or tickets to an event.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: opening hours
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment:
The opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.
- Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
- Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
- Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
- If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: opening hours specification

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: operating system

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: owned from

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: owns

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: part of season

ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: pathophysiology

ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: physiological benefits
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: postal code
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The postal code. For example, 94043.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: predecessor of
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: pregnancy category
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Pregnancy category of this drug.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: pregnancy warning
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: prep time
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The length of time it takes to prepare the recipe, in ISO 8601 duration format.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: preparation
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: prescription status
ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether this drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter.

ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: item list element

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: latitude

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: legal name

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: line

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: logo

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: longitude

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: memory requirements

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: menu

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: naics

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: natural progression

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: overdosage

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: overview

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: player type

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: polygon

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: population

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: possible complication

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: post office box number

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: print column

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: print page
DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: print section
DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: procedure
DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: processor requirements
DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: product ID

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: proficiency level
DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: proprietary name

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH <a href=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html>publication type catalog.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: qualifications

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: recipe instructions

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: recommendation strength

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: related link

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: review count

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: serves cuisine

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: serving size

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: significant link

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: skills
DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Skills required to fulfill this role.

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: sku

DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: street address

Class.rdfs:label: APIReference
Class.rdfs:comment: Reference documentation for application programming interfaces (APIs).

Class.rdfs:label: Administrative area
Class.rdfs:comment: A geographical region under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

Class.rdfs:label: Aggregate offer
Class.rdfs:comment: When a single product that has different offers (for example, the same pair of shoes is offered by different merchants), then AggregateOffer can be used.

Class.rdfs:label: Aggregate rating
Class.rdfs:comment: The average rating based on multiple ratings or reviews.

Class.rdfs:label: Alignment object
Class.rdfs:comment: An intangible item that describes an alignment between a learning resource and a node in an educational framework.

Class.rdfs:label: Anatomical structure
Class.rdfs:comment: Any part of the human body, typically a component of an anatomical system. Organs, tissues, and cells are all anatomical structures.

Class.rdfs:label: Anatomical system
Class.rdfs:comment: An anatomical system is a group of anatomical structures that work together to perform a certain task. Anatomical systems, such as organ systems, are one organizing principle of anatomy, and can includes circulatory, digestive, endocrine, integumentary, immune, lymphatic, muscular, nervous, reproductive, respiratory, skeletal, urinary, vestibular, and other systems.

Class.rdfs:label: Approved indication
Class.rdfs:comment: An indication for a medical therapy that has been formally specified or approved by a regulatory body that regulates use of the therapy; for example, the US FDA approves indications for most drugs in the US.

Class.rdfs:label: Artery
Class.rdfs:comment: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood away from the heart.

Class.rdfs:label: Article
Class.rdfs:comment: An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.

Class.rdfs:label: Audience
Class.rdfs:comment: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

Class.rdfs:label: Blood test
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical test performed on a sample of a patient's blood.

Class.rdfs:label: Body of water
Class.rdfs:comment: A body of water, such as a sea, ocean, or lake.

Class.rdfs:label: Bone
Class.rdfs:comment: Rigid connective tissue that comprises up the skeletal structure of the human body.

Class.rdfs:label: Book format type
Class.rdfs:comment: The publication format of the book.

Class.rdfs:label: Brain structure
Class.rdfs:comment: Any anatomical structure which pertains to the soft nervous tissue functioning as the coordinating center of sensation and intellectual and nervous activity.

Class.rdfs:label: Brand
Class.rdfs:comment: A brand is a name used by an organization or business person for labeling a product, product group, or similar.

Class.rdfs:label: Business entity type
Class.rdfs:comment:
A business entity type is a conceptual entity representing the legal form, the size, the main line of business, the position in the value chain, or any combination thereof, of an organization or business person.
Commonly used values:
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Business http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Enduser http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PublicInstitution http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Reseller

Class.rdfs:label: Business function
Class.rdfs:comment:
The business function specifies the type of activity or access (i.e., the bundle of rights) offered by the organization or business person through the offer. Typical are sell, rental or lease, maintenance or repair, manufacture / produce, recycle / dispose, engineering / construction, or installation. Proprietary specifications of access rights are also instances of this class.
Commonly used values:
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ConstructionInstallation http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Dispose http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#LeaseOut http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Maintain http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ProvideService http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Repair http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Buy

Class.rdfs:label: Canal
Class.rdfs:comment: A canal, like the Panama Canal

Class.rdfs:label: Civic structure
Class.rdfs:comment: A public structure, such as a town hall or concert hall.

Class.rdfs:label: Code
Class.rdfs:comment: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

Class.rdfs:label: College or university
Class.rdfs:comment: A college, university, or other third-level educational institution.

Class.rdfs:label: Comment
Class.rdfs:comment: A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment's content is expressed via the "text" property, and its topic via "about", properties shared with all CreativeWorks.

Class.rdfs:label: Contact point
Class.rdfs:comment: A contact point—for example, a Customer Complaints department.

Class.rdfs:label: Continent
Class.rdfs:comment: One of the continents (for example, Europe or Africa).

Class.rdfs:label: Creative work
Class.rdfs:comment: The most generic kind of creative work, including books, movies, photographs, software programs, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Credit card
Class.rdfs:comment:
A credit or debit card type as a standardized procedure for transferring the monetary amount for a purchase.
Commonly used values:
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#AmericanExpress http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DinersClub http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Discover http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#JCB http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#MasterCard http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#VISA

Class.rdfs:label: DDx element
Class.rdfs:comment: An alternative, closely-related condition typically considered later in the differential diagnosis process along with the signs that are used to distinguish it.

Class.rdfs:label: Dance group
Class.rdfs:comment: A dance group—for example, the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater or Riverdance.

Class.rdfs:label: Data type
Class.rdfs:comment: The basic data types such as Integers, Strings, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Dataset
Class.rdfs:comment: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

Class.rdfs:label: Date
Class.rdfs:comment: A date value in ISO 8601 date format.

Class.rdfs:label: Date time
Class.rdfs:comment: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm] (see Chapter 5.4 of ISO 8601).

Class.rdfs:label: Day of week
Class.rdfs:comment:
The day of the week, e.g. used to specify to which day the opening hours of an OpeningHoursSpecification refer.
Commonly used values:
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Monday http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Tuesday http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Wednesday http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Thursday http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Friday http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Saturday http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sunday http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PublicHolidays

Class.rdfs:label: Defence establishment
Class.rdfs:comment: A defence establishment, such as an army or navy base.

Class.rdfs:label: Delivery charge specification
Class.rdfs:comment: The price for the delivery of an offer using a particular delivery method.

Class.rdfs:label: Delivery method
Class.rdfs:comment:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfilment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.
Commonly used values:
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeMail http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeOwnFleet http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModePickUp http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

Class.rdfs:label: Demand
Class.rdfs:comment: A demand entity represents the public, not necessarily binding, not necessarily exclusive, announcement by an organization or person to seek a certain type of goods or services. For describing demand using this type, the very same properties used for Offer apply.

Class.rdfs:label: Diagnostic lab
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical laboratory that offers on-site or off-site diagnostic services.

Class.rdfs:label: Diagnostic procedure
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical procedure intended primarly for diagnostic, as opposed to therapeutic, purposes.

Class.rdfs:label: Diet
Class.rdfs:comment: A strategy of regulating the intake of food to achieve or maintain a specific health-related goal.

Class.rdfs:label: Dietary supplement
Class.rdfs:comment: A product taken by mouth that contains a dietary ingredient intended to supplement the diet. Dietary ingredients may include vitamins, minerals, herbs or other botanicals, amino acids, and substances such as enzymes, organ tissues, glandulars and metabolites.

Class.rdfs:label: Distance
Class.rdfs:comment: Properties that take Distances as values are of the form '<Number> <Length unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 ft'

Class.rdfs:label: Dose schedule
Class.rdfs:comment: A specific dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug
Class.rdfs:comment: A chemical or biologic substance, used as a medical therapy, that has a physiological effect on an organism.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug class
Class.rdfs:comment: A class of medical drugs, e.g., statins. Classes can represent general pharmacological class, common mechanisms of action, common physiological effects, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug cost
Class.rdfs:comment: The cost per unit of a medical drug. Note that this type is not meant to represent the price in an offer of a drug for sale; see the Offer type for that. This type will typically be used to tag wholesale or average retail cost of a drug, or maximum reimbursable cost. Costs of medical drugs vary widely depending on how and where they are paid for, so while this type captures some of the variables, costs should be used with caution by consumers of this schema's markup.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug cost category
Class.rdfs:comment: Enumerated categories of medical drug costs.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug legal status
Class.rdfs:comment: The legal availability status of a medical drug.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug pregnancy category
Class.rdfs:comment: Categories that represent an assessment of the risk of fetal injury due to a drug or pharmaceutical used as directed by the mother during pregnancy.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug prescription status
Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether this drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter.

Class.rdfs:label: Drug strength
Class.rdfs:comment: A specific strength in which a medical drug is available in a specific country.

Class.rdfs:label: Emergency service
Class.rdfs:comment: An emergency service, such as a fire station or ER.

Class.rdfs:label: Energy
Class.rdfs:comment: Properties that take Enerygy as values are of the form '<Number> <Energy unit of measure>'

Class.rdfs:label: Enumeration
Class.rdfs:comment: Lists or enumerations—for example, a list of cuisines or music genres, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Event
Class.rdfs:comment: An event happening at a certain time at a certain location.

Class.rdfs:label: Exercise plan
Class.rdfs:comment: Fitness-related activity designed for a specific health-related purpose, including defined exercise routines as well as activity prescribed by a clinician.

Class.rdfs:label: Geo coordinates
Class.rdfs:comment: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

Class.rdfs:label: Geo shape
Class.rdfs:comment: The geographic shape of a place.

Class.rdfs:label: Government office
Class.rdfs:comment: A government office—for example, an IRS or DMV office.

Class.rdfs:label: Image gallery
Class.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Image gallery page.

Class.rdfs:label: Imaging test
Class.rdfs:comment: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes.

Class.rdfs:label: Individual product
Class.rdfs:comment: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

Class.rdfs:label: Infectious agent class
Class.rdfs:comment: Classes of agents or pathogens that transmit infectious diseases. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Infectious disease
Class.rdfs:comment: An infectious disease is a clinically evident human disease resulting from the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, like pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and prions. To be considered an infectious disease, such pathogens are known to be able to cause this disease.

Class.rdfs:label: Intangible
Class.rdfs:comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Item availability
Class.rdfs:comment: A list of possible product availablity options.

Class.rdfs:label: Item list
Class.rdfs:comment: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

Class.rdfs:label: Item page
Class.rdfs:comment: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.

Class.rdfs:label: Job posting
Class.rdfs:comment: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

Class.rdfs:label: Joint
Class.rdfs:comment: The anatomical location at which two or more bones make contact.

Class.rdfs:label: Landform
Class.rdfs:comment: A landform or physical feature. Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.

Class.rdfs:label: Language
Class.rdfs:comment: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. and programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp.

Class.rdfs:label: Legislative building
Class.rdfs:comment: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

Class.rdfs:label: Lifestyle modification
Class.rdfs:comment: A process of care involving exercise, changes to diet, fitness routines, and other lifestyle changes aimed at improving a health condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Ligament
Class.rdfs:comment: A short band of tough, flexible, fibrous connective tissue that functions to connect multiple bones, cartilages, and structurally support joints.

Class.rdfs:label: Local business
Class.rdfs:comment: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Lodging business
Class.rdfs:comment: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

Class.rdfs:label: Lymphatic vessel
Class.rdfs:comment: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries lymph fluid unidirectionally toward the heart.

Class.rdfs:label: Mass
Class.rdfs:comment: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'

Class.rdfs:label: Maximum dose schedule
Class.rdfs:comment: The maximum dosing schedule considered safe for a drug or supplement as recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

Class.rdfs:label: Media object
Class.rdfs:comment: An image, video, or audio object embedded in a web page. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

Class.rdfs:label: Medical audience
Class.rdfs:comment: Target audiences for medical web pages. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical cause
Class.rdfs:comment:
The causative agent(s) that are responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in a medical condition, symptom or sign. In this schema, unless otherwise specified this is meant to be the proximate cause of the medical condition, symptom or sign. The proximate cause is defined as the causative agent that most directly results in the medical condition, symptom or sign. For example, the HIV virus could be considered a cause of AIDS. Or in a diagnostic context, if a patient fell and sustained a hip fracture and two days later sustained a pulmonary embolism which eventuated in a cardiac arrest, the cause of the cardiac arrest (the proximate cause) would be the pulmonary embolism and not the fall.

Medical causes can include cardiovascular, chemical, dermatologic, endocrine, environmental, gastroenterologic, genetic, hematologic, gynecologic, iatrogenic, infectious, musculoskeletal, neurologic, nutritional, obstetric, oncologic, otolaryngologic, pharmacologic, psychiatric, pulmonary, renal, rheumatologic, toxic, traumatic, or urologic causes; medical conditions can be causes as well.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical code
Class.rdfs:comment: A code for a medical entity.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical condition
Class.rdfs:comment: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical condition stage
Class.rdfs:comment: A stage of a medical condition, such as 'Stage IIIa'.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical contraindication
Class.rdfs:comment: A condition or factor that serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical therapy. Contraindications can be absolute (there are no reasonable circumstances for undertaking a course of action) or relative (the patient is at higher risk of complications, but that these risks may be outweighed by other considerations or mitigated by other measures).

Class.rdfs:label: Medical device
Class.rdfs:comment: Any object used in a medical capacity, such as to diagnose or treat a patient.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical device purpose
Class.rdfs:comment: Categories of medical devices, organized by the purpose or intended use of the device.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical entity
Class.rdfs:comment: The most generic type of entity related to health and the practice of medicine.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical enumeration
Class.rdfs:comment: Enumerations related to health and the practice of medicine.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical evidence level
Class.rdfs:comment: Level of evidence for a medical guideline. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical guideline
Class.rdfs:comment: Any recommendation made by a standard society (e.g. ACC/AHA) or consensus statement that denotes how to diagnose and treat a particular condition. Note: this type should be used to tag the actual guideline recommendation; if the guideline recommendation occurs in a larger scholarly article, use MedicalScholarlyArticle to tag the overall article, not this type. Note also: the organization making the recommendation should be captured in the recognizingAuthority base property of MedicalEntity.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical guideline contraindication
Class.rdfs:comment: A guideline contraindication that designates a process as harmful and where quality of the data supporting the contraindication is sound.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical guideline recommendation
Class.rdfs:comment: A guideline recommendation that is regarded as efficacious and where quality of the data supporting the recommendation is sound.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical imaging technique
Class.rdfs:comment: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical indication
Class.rdfs:comment: A condition or factor that indicates use of a medical therapy, including signs, symptoms, risk factors, anatomical states, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical intangible
Class.rdfs:comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things in the medical space.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical observational study
Class.rdfs:comment: An observational study is a type of medical study that attempts to infer the possible effect of a treatment through observation of a cohort of subjects over a period of time. In an observational study, the assignment of subjects into treatment groups versus control groups is outside the control of the investigator. This is in contrast with controlled studies, such as the randomized controlled trials represented by MedicalTrial, where each subject is randomly assigned to a treatment group or a control group before the start of the treatment.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical observational study design
Class.rdfs:comment: Design models for observational medical studies. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical organization
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical organization, such as a doctor's office or clinic.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical procedure
Class.rdfs:comment: A process of care used in either a diagnostic, therapeutic, or palliative capacity that relies on invasive (surgical), non-invasive, or percutaneous techniques.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical procedure type
Class.rdfs:comment: An enumeration that describes different types of medical procedures.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical risk calculator
Class.rdfs:comment: A complex mathematical calculation requiring an online calculator, used to assess prognosis. Note: use the url property of Thing to record any URLs for online calculators.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical risk estimator
Class.rdfs:comment: Any rule set or interactive tool for estimating the risk of developing a complication or condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical risk factor
Class.rdfs:comment: A risk factor is anything that increases a person's likelihood of developing or contracting a disease, medical condition, or complication.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical risk score
Class.rdfs:comment: A simple system that adds up the number of risk factors to yield a score that is associated with prognosis, e.g. CHAD score, TIMI risk score.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical scholarly article
Class.rdfs:comment: A scholarly article in the medical domain.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical sign
Class.rdfs:comment: Any physical manifestation of a person's medical condition discoverable by objective diagnostic tests or physical examination.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical sign or symptom
Class.rdfs:comment: Any indication of the existence of a medical condition or disease.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical specialty
Class.rdfs:comment: Any specific branch of medical science or practice. Medical specialities include clinical specialties that pertain to particular organ systems and their respective disease states, as well as allied health specialties. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical study
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical study is an umbrella type covering all kinds of research studies relating to human medicine or health, including observational studies and interventional trials and registries, randomized, controlled or not. When the specific type of study is known, use one of the extensions of this type, such as MedicalTrial or MedicalObservationalStudy. Also, note that this type should be used to mark up data that describes the study itself; to tag an article that publishes the results of a study, use MedicalScholarlyArticle. Note: use the code property of MedicalEntity to store study IDs, e.g. clinicaltrials.gov ID.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical study status
Class.rdfs:comment: The status of a medical study. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical symptom
Class.rdfs:comment: Any indication of the existence of a medical condition or disease that is apparent to the patient.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical test
Class.rdfs:comment: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical test panel
Class.rdfs:comment: Any collection of tests commonly ordered together.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical therapy
Class.rdfs:comment: Any medical intervention designed to prevent, treat, and cure human diseases and medical conditions, including both curative and palliative therapies. Medical therapies are typically processes of care relying upon pharmacotherapy, behavioral therapy, supportive therapy (with fluid or nutrition for example), or detoxification (e.g. hemodialysis) aimed at improving or preventing a health condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical trial
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical trial is a type of medical study that uses scientific process used to compare the safety and efficacy of medical therapies or medical procedures. In general, medical trials are controlled and subjects are allocated at random to the different treatment and/or control groups.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical trial design
Class.rdfs:comment: Design models for medical trials. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Medical web page
Class.rdfs:comment: A web page that provides medical information.

Class.rdfs:label: Mountain
Class.rdfs:comment: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest

Class.rdfs:label: Muscle
Class.rdfs:comment: A muscle is an anatomical structure consisting of a contractile form of tissue that animals use to effect movement.

Class.rdfs:label: Music group
Class.rdfs:comment: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

Class.rdfs:label: Music playlist
Class.rdfs:comment: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

Class.rdfs:label: Music recording
Class.rdfs:comment: A music recording (track), usually a single song.

Class.rdfs:label: Nerve
Class.rdfs:comment: A common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons.

Class.rdfs:label: Offer
Class.rdfs:comment: An offer to sell an item—for example, an offer to sell a product, the DVD of a movie, or tickets to an event.

Class.rdfs:label: Offer item condition
Class.rdfs:comment: A list of possible conditions for the item for sale.

Class.rdfs:label: Opening hours specification
Class.rdfs:comment: A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.

Class.rdfs:label: Organization
Class.rdfs:comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Ownership info
Class.rdfs:comment: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

Class.rdfs:label: Palliative procedure
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical procedure intended primarly for palliative purposes, aimed at relieving the symptoms of an underlying health condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Parcel service
Class.rdfs:comment:
A private parcel service as the delivery mode available for a certain offer.
Commonly used values:
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

Class.rdfs:label: Parent audience
Class.rdfs:comment: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content

Class.rdfs:label: Parking facility
Class.rdfs:comment: A parking lot or other parking facility.

Class.rdfs:label: Pathology test
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical test performed by a laboratory that typically involves examination of a tissue sample by a pathologist.

Class.rdfs:label: Payment charge specification
Class.rdfs:comment: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

Class.rdfs:label: Payment method
Class.rdfs:comment:
A payment method is a standardized procedure for transferring the monetary amount for a purchase. Payment methods are characterized by the legal and technical structures used, and by the organization or group carrying out the transaction.
Commonly used values:
http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByBankTransferInAdvance http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByInvoice http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Cash http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#CheckInAdvance http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#COD http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DirectDebit http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#GoogleCheckout http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PayPal http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PaySwarm

Class.rdfs:label: People audience
Class.rdfs:comment: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

Class.rdfs:label: Performing arts theater
Class.rdfs:comment: A theatre or other performing art center.

Class.rdfs:label: Performing group
Class.rdfs:comment: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

Class.rdfs:label: Person
Class.rdfs:comment: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

Class.rdfs:label: Physical activity
Class.rdfs:comment: Any bodily activity that enhances or maintains physical fitness and overall health and wellness. Includes activity that is part of daily living and routine, structured exercise, and exercise prescribed as part of a medical treatment or recovery plan.

Class.rdfs:label: Physical activity category
Class.rdfs:comment: Categories of physical activity, organized by physiologic classification.

Class.rdfs:label: Physical exam
Class.rdfs:comment: A type of physical examination of a patient performed by a physician. Enumerated type.

Class.rdfs:label: Physical therapy
Class.rdfs:comment: A process of progressive physical care and rehabilitation aimed at improving a health condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Place
Class.rdfs:comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

Class.rdfs:label: Place of worship
Class.rdfs:comment: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.

Class.rdfs:label: Prevention indication
Class.rdfs:comment: An indication for preventing an underlying condition, symptom, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Price specification
Class.rdfs:comment: A structured value representing a monetary amount. Typically, only the subclasses of this type are used for markup.

Class.rdfs:label: Product
Class.rdfs:comment: A product is anything that is made available for saleâfor example, a pair of shoes, a concert ticket, or a car. Commodity services, like haircuts, can also be represented using this type.

Class.rdfs:label: Product model
Class.rdfs:comment: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

Class.rdfs:label: Psychological treatment
Class.rdfs:comment: A process of care relying upon counseling, dialogue, communication, verbalization aimed at improving a mental health condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Qualitative value
Class.rdfs:comment: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the the power cord plug type "US" or the garment sizes "S", "M", "L", and "XL"

Class.rdfs:label: Quantitative value
Class.rdfs:comment: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

Class.rdfs:label: Quantity
Class.rdfs:comment: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 Kg' or '4 milligrams'.

Class.rdfs:label: Radiation therapy
Class.rdfs:comment: A process of care using radiation aimed at improving a health condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Recommended dose schedule
Class.rdfs:comment: A recommended dosing schedule for a drug or supplement as prescribed or recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

Class.rdfs:label: Reported dose schedule
Class.rdfs:comment: A patient-reported or observed dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

Class.rdfs:label: Reservoir
Class.rdfs:comment: A reservoir, like the Lake Kariba reservoir.

Class.rdfs:label: Residence
Class.rdfs:comment: The place where a person lives.

Class.rdfs:label: Review
Class.rdfs:comment: A review of an item - for example, a restaurant, movie, or store.

Class.rdfs:label: River body of water
Class.rdfs:comment: A river (for example, the broad majestic Shannon).

Class.rdfs:label: Sea body of water
Class.rdfs:comment: A sea (for example, the Caspian sea).

Class.rdfs:label: Search results page
Class.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Search results page.

Class.rdfs:label: Site navigation element
Class.rdfs:comment: A navigation element of the page.

Class.rdfs:label: Some products
Class.rdfs:comment: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

Class.rdfs:label: Specialty
Class.rdfs:comment: Any branch of a field in which people typically develop specific expertise, usually after significant study, time, and effort.

Class.rdfs:label: Sports activity location
Class.rdfs:comment: A sports location, such as a playing field.

Class.rdfs:label: Structured value
Class.rdfs:comment: Structured values are strings—for example, addresses—that have certain constraints on their structure.

Class.rdfs:label: Superficial anatomy
Class.rdfs:comment: Anatomical features that can be observed by sight (without dissection), including the form and proportions of the human body as well as surface landmarks that correspond to deeper subcutaneous structures. Superficial anatomy plays an important role in sports medicine, phlebotomy, and other medical specialties as underlying anatomical structures can be identified through surface palpation. For example, during back surgery, superficial anatomy can be used to palpate and count vertebrae to find the site of incision. Or in phlebotomy, superficial anatomy can be used to locate an underlying vein; for example, the median cubital vein can be located by palpating the borders of the cubital fossa (such as the epicondyles of the humerus) and then looking for the superficial signs of the vein, such as size, prominence, ability to refill after depression, and feel of surrounding tissue support. As another example, in a subluxation (dislocation) of the glenohumeral joint, the bony structure becomes pronounced with the deltoid muscle failing to cover the glenohumeral joint allowing the edges of the scapula to be superficially visible. Here, the superficial anatomy is the visible edges of the scapula, implying the underlying dislocation of the joint (the related anatomical structure).

Class.rdfs:label: TVEpisode
Class.rdfs:comment: An episode of a TV series or season.

Class.rdfs:label: Tech article
Class.rdfs:comment: A technical article - Example: How-to (task) topics, step-by-step, procedural troubleshooting, specifications, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Theater group
Class.rdfs:comment: A theater group or company—for example, the Royal Shakespeare Company or Druid Theatre.

Class.rdfs:label: Therapeutic procedure
Class.rdfs:comment: A medical procedure intended primarly for therapeutic purposes, aimed at improving a health condition.

Class.rdfs:label: Time
Class.rdfs:comment: A point in time recurring on multiple days in the form hh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm] (see XML schema for details).

Class.rdfs:label: Treatment indication
Class.rdfs:comment: An indication for treating an underlying condition, symptom, etc.

Class.rdfs:label: Type and quantity node
Class.rdfs:comment: A structured value indicating the quantity, unit of measurement, and business function of goods included in a bundle offer.

Class.rdfs:label: Unit price specification
Class.rdfs:comment: The price asked for a given offer by the respective organization or person.

Class.rdfs:label: User checkins
Class.rdfs:comment: User interaction: Check-in at a place.

Class.rdfs:label: User comments
Class.rdfs:comment: The UserInteraction event in which a user comments on an item.

Class.rdfs:label: User downloads
Class.rdfs:comment: User interaction: Download of an item.

Class.rdfs:label: User interaction
Class.rdfs:comment: A user interacting with a page

Class.rdfs:label: User page visits
Class.rdfs:comment: User interaction: Visit to a web page.

Class.rdfs:label: User plays
Class.rdfs:comment: User interaction: Play count of an item, for example a video or a song.

Class.rdfs:label: Vein
Class.rdfs:comment: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood to the heart.

Class.rdfs:label: Vessel
Class.rdfs:comment: A component of the human body circulatory system comprised of an intricate network of hollow tubes that transport blood throughout the entire body.

Class.rdfs:label: Video gallery
Class.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Video gallery page.

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Case series
NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A case series (also known as a clinical series) is a medical research study that tracks patients with a known exposure given similar treatment or examines their medical records for exposure and outcome. A case series can be retrospective or prospective and usually involves a smaller number of patients than the more powerful case-control studies or randomized controlled trials. Case series may be consecutive or non-consecutive, depending on whether all cases presenting to the reporting authors over a period of time were included, or only a selection.

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Cohort study
NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Also known as a panel study. A cohort study is a form of longitudinal study used in medicine and social science. It is one type of study design and should be compared with a cross-sectional study. A cohort is a group of people who share a common characteristic or experience within a defined period (e.g., are born, leave school, lose their job, are exposed to a drug or a vaccine, etc.). The comparison group may be the general population from which the cohort is drawn, or it may be another cohort of persons thought to have had little or no exposure to the substance under investigation, but otherwise similar. Alternatively, subgroups within the cohort may be compared with each other.

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FDAcategory b
NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A designation by the US FDA signifying that animal reproduction studies have failed to demonstrate a risk to the fetus and there are no adequate and well-controlled studies in pregnant women.

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FDAcategory c
NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A designation by the US FDA signifying that animal reproduction studies have shown an adverse effect on the fetus and there are no adequate and well-controlled studies in humans, but potential benefits may warrant use of the drug in pregnant women despite potential risks.

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FDAcategory d
NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A designation by the US FDA signifying that there is positive evidence of human fetal risk based on adverse reaction data from investigational or marketing experience or studies in humans, but potential benefits may warrant use of the drug in pregnant women despite potential risks.

NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FDAcategory x
NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A designation by the US FDA signifying that studies in animals or humans have demonstrated fetal abnormalities and/or there is positive evidence of human fetal risk based on adverse reaction data from investigational or marketing experience, and the risks involved in use of the drug in pregnant women clearly outweigh potential benefits.
